import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['miles'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['year'], data['gas'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Gas')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between the age of the car and the amount of gas used?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    avg_gas_per_mile = data['gas_per_mile'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(data['year'], data['gas_per_mile'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_gas_per_mile, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average gas per mile: {avg_gas_per_mile:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Gas per mile')
    ax.set_title('What is the average gas consumption per mile?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    avg_miles_per_year = data.groupby('year')['miles'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_miles_per_year['year'], avg_miles_per_year['miles'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=avg_miles_per_year['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Miles Driven')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Miles Driven')
    ax.set_title('What is the average miles driven per year?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
